descript.abstract: Hospital locations. Includes public and private hospitals in the region. Includes only hospitals with an emergency room.

idinfo.useconst: This database and GIS data are made available under the Open Database License (ODbL v1) and Database Content License (DbCL v1). See http://www.oregonmetro.gov/rlis-live.

browse.browsed: City halls, fire stations and hospitals shown with streets and rivers for orientation.

horizpa.horizpar: Registered to tax lots. Street center lines were digitized from aerial orthophotography at +/- 10 feet accuracy. Tax lots were fit to the street centerlines. Beaverton, Oregon City and Tigard planning areas were improved to +/- 5 feet accuracy. Multnomah County was created with coordinate geometry using better control.

procstep.procdesc: Projection information (.prj file), compatible with ArcGIS 8.1, was added to the layer.
Locations adjusted using 2000 Spencer Gross aerial photography and attribute data verified by Trimet.
In coverage the Zip item modified from binary to character type. In the derived shapefile and SDE_layer the Zipcode field was also modified to a character type.
Data now maintained and provided by TriMet. Expanded widths of Name, Address and City fields.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: City in which the hospital is located.
United States Postal Service ZIP Code.

distinfo.distliab: The information in this file was derived from digital databases on Metro's GIS. Care was taken in the creation of this file. Metro cannot accept any responsibility for errors, omissions, or positional accuracy. There are no warranties, expressed or implied.

onlinopt.accinstr: Email drc@oregonmetro.gov or call 503-797-1742 for further instructions.
